'''Orthogonal collocation''' is a method for the [[numerical partial differential equations|numerical solution of partial differential equations]]. It uses [[collocation method|collocation]] at the zeros of some [[orthogonal polynomials]] to transform the [[partial differential equation]] (PDE) to a set of [[ordinary differential equation]]s (ODEs). The ODEs can then be solved by any method. It has been shown that it is usually advantageous to choose the collocation points as the zeros of the corresponding [[Jacobi polynomial]] (independent of the PDE system).

